{"title_page": "Byron Center, Michigan", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text=[[Byron, Michigan]] in Shiawassee County.}}\n{{distinguish|text=[[Byron Township, Michigan|Byron Township]], a civil township containing Byron Center}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Byron Center, Michigan\n|settlement_type          = [[Census-designated place]] (CDP) & [[unincorporated area|unincorporated community]]\n|image_skyline            = \n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_map                = Kent_County_Michigan_Incorporated_and_Unincorporated_areas_Byron_Center_Highlighted.svg\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of Byron Center, Michigan\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|coordinates              = {{coord|42|48|44|N|85|43|22|W|type:city_region:US-MI_source:GNIS|display=inline}}\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Michigan|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Kent County, Michigan|Kent]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Michigan]]\n|subdivision_type3        = [[List of townships in Michigan|Township]]\n|subdivision_name3        = [[Byron Township, Michigan|Byron]]\n\n<!-- Government -->\n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = \n|leader_name              = \n|leader_title1            = \n|leader_name1             = \n|unit_pref  =  Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = \n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 13.0\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 5.0\n|area_land_km2            = 13.0\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 5.0\n|area_water_km2           = 0.0\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.0\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 227\n|elevation_ft             = 745\n|population_total         = 5822\n|population_as_of         = [[United States Census, 2010|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_density_km2   = 447.8\n|population_density_sq_mi = 1164.4\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 49315\n|area_code                = [[Area code 616|616]]\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|timezone                 = [[North American Eastern Time Zone|Eastern (EST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -5\n|timezone_DST             = EDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -4\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 26-12280<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212221153/http://factfinder.census.gov/main.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2020-02-12 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=2008-01-31 |title=American FactFinder }}</ref>\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 0622409<ref>{{gnis|0622409}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Byron Center''' is an [[Unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] in [[Kent County, Michigan|Kent County]] in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Michigan]]. It is a [[census-designated place]] (CDP) used for statistical purposes. The population was 5,822 at the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]].\n\nThe community is at the center of [[Byron Township, Michigan|Byron Township]], about {{convert|14|mi|km}} south-southwest of [[Grand Rapids, Michigan|Grand Rapids]]. The Byron Center [[ZIP code]] is 49315, although the area served by the ZIP code also includes most of Byron Township as well as portions of [[Gaines Township, Kent County, Michigan|Gaines Township]] to the east in Kent County, and [[Jamestown Township, Ottawa County, Michigan|Jamestown Township]] to the west in [[Ottawa County, Michigan|Ottawa County]] and portions of [[Salem Township, Allegan County, Michigan|Salem Township]] to the southwest and [[Dorr Township, Allegan County, Michigan|Dorr Township]] to the south in [[Allegan County, Michigan|Allegan County]].<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/MapItDrawServlet?geo_id=86000US49315&_bucket_id=50&tree_id=420&context=AdvSearch&_lang=en 49315 5-Digit ZCTA, 493 3-Digit ZCTA - Reference Map - American FactFinder]{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, U.S. Census Bureau, 2000 census</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Byron Center has a total area of {{convert|5.0|sqmi|km2}}, all land.\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of the 2010 census Byron Center had a population of 5,822. The population was 93.7% non-Hispanic white, 0.9% African-American, 0.4% Native American, 1.0% Asian, 0.1% non-Hispanics of some other race, 1.4% reporting two or more races and 2.7% Hispanic.<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?src=CF 2010 fact finder report on Byron Center] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129082905/http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?src=CF |date=November 29, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\" /> of 2000, there were 3,777 people, 1,322 households, and 1,040 families residing in Byron Center.  The [[population density]] was 751.8 per square mile (290.5/km\u00b2).  There were 1,374 housing units at an average density of 273.5 per square mile (105.7/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the CDP was 97.93% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.11% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.19% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.61% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.03% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.21% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.93% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.95% of the population.\n\nThere were 1,322 households out of which 43.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 69.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.3% had a female householder with no husband present, and 21.3% were non-families. 19.4% of all households were made up of individuals and 9.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.82 and the average family size was 3.26.\n\nAround 32.5% of Byron Center residents are under the age of 18, 6.5% from 18 to 24, 30.6% from 25 to 44, 18.9% from 45 to 64, and 11.5% are 65 years of age or older.  The median age is 34 years. For every 100 females, there are 90.6 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there are 89.0 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in Byron Center was $58,508, and the median income for a family was $65,882. Males had a median income of $50,517 versus $28,043 for females. The [[per capita income]] was $29,028.  About 1.9% of families and 3.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 6.7% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.byrontownship.org/|Byron Township official website}}\n*[http://www.byroncenterhistory.com/ Byron Area Historic Museum]\n\n{{Kent County, Michigan}}\n\n{{Coord|42|48|44|N|85|43|22|W|type:city_region:US-MI_source:GNIS|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Kent County, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Grand Rapids metropolitan area]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Kent County, Michigan]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|text=[[Byron, Michigan]] in Shiawassee County.}}\n{{distinguish|text=[[Byron Township, Michigan|Byron Township]], a civil township containing Byron Center}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Byron Center, Michigan\n|settlement_type          = [[Census-designated place]]\n|image_skyline            = \n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_map                = Kent_County_Michigan_Incorporated_and_Unincorporated_areas_Byron_Center_Highlighted.svg\n|mapsize                  = 250px\n|map_caption              = Location of Byron Center, Michigan\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|coordinates              = {{coord|42|48|44|N|85|43|22|W|type:city_region:US-MI_source:GNIS|display=inline}}\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Michigan|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Kent County, Michigan|Kent]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Michigan]]\n|subdivision_type3        = [[List of townships in Michigan|Township]]\n|subdivision_name3        = [[Byron Township, Michigan|Byron]]\n\n<!-- Government -->\n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = \n|leader_name              = \n|leader_title1            = \n|leader_name1             = \n|unit_pref  =  Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = \n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 13.0\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 5.0\n|area_land_km2            = 13.0\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 5.0\n|area_water_km2           = 0.0\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.0\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 227\n|elevation_ft             = 745\n|population_total         = 5822\n|population_as_of         = [[United States Census, 2010|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_density_km2   = 447.8\n|population_density_sq_mi = 1164.4\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 49315\n|area_code                = [[Area code 616|616]]\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|timezone                 = [[North American Eastern Time Zone|Eastern (EST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -5\n|timezone_DST             = EDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -4\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 26-12280<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web |url=http://factfinder.census.gov |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212221153/http://factfinder.census.gov/main.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2020-02-12 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]] |accessdate=2008-01-31 |title=American FactFinder }}</ref>\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = 0622409<ref>{{gnis|0622409}}</ref>\n}}\n'''Byron Center''' is an [[Unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] in [[Kent County, Michigan|Kent County]] in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Michigan]]. It is a [[census-designated place]] (CDP) used for statistical purposes. The population was 5,822 at the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]].\n\nThe community is at the center of [[Byron Township, Michigan|Byron Township]], about {{convert|14|mi|km}} south-southwest of [[Grand Rapids, Michigan|Grand Rapids]]. The Byron Center [[ZIP code]] is 49315, although the area served by the ZIP code also includes most of Byron Township as well as portions of [[Gaines Township, Kent County, Michigan|Gaines Township]] to the east in Kent County, and [[Jamestown Township, Ottawa County, Michigan|Jamestown Township]] to the west in [[Ottawa County, Michigan|Ottawa County]] and portions of [[Salem Township, Allegan County, Michigan|Salem Township]] to the southwest and [[Dorr Township, Allegan County, Michigan|Dorr Township]] to the south in [[Allegan County, Michigan|Allegan County]].<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/MapItDrawServlet?geo_id=86000US49315&_bucket_id=50&tree_id=420&context=AdvSearch&_lang=en 49315 5-Digit ZCTA, 493 3-Digit ZCTA - Reference Map - American FactFinder]{{Dead link|date=March 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, U.S. Census Bureau, 2000 census</ref>\n\n==Geography==\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Byron Center has a total area of {{convert|5.0|sqmi|km2}}, all land.\n\n==Demographics==\nAs of the 2010 census Byron Center had a population of 5,822. The population was 93.7% non-Hispanic white, 0.9% African-American, 0.4% Native American, 1.0% Asian, 0.1% non-Hispanics of some other race, 1.4% reporting two or more races and 2.7% Hispanic.<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?src=CF 2010 fact finder report on Byron Center] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141129082905/http://factfinder.census.gov/faces/tableservices/jsf/pages/productview.xhtml?src=CF |date=November 29, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\" /> of 2000, there were 3,777 people, 1,322 households, and 1,040 families residing in Byron Center.  The [[population density]] was 751.8 per square mile (290.5/km\u00b2).  There were 1,374 housing units at an average density of 273.5 per square mile (105.7/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the CDP was 97.93% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.11% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.19% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.61% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.03% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 0.21% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 0.93% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.95% of the population.\n\nThere were 1,322 households out of which 43.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 69.5% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 7.3% had a female householder with no husband present, and 21.3% were non-families. 19.4% of all households were made up of individuals and 9.6% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 2.82 and the average family size was 3.26.\n\nAround 32.5% of Byron Center residents are under the age of 18, 6.5% from 18 to 24, 30.6% from 25 to 44, 18.9% from 45 to 64, and 11.5% are 65 years of age or older.  The median age is 34 years. For every 100 females, there are 90.6 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there are 89.0 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in Byron Center was $58,508, and the median income for a family was $65,882. Males had a median income of $50,517 versus $28,043 for females. The [[per capita income]] was $29,028.  About 1.9% of families and 3.2% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 6.7% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://www.byrontownship.org/|Byron Township official website}}\n*[http://www.byroncenterhistory.com/ Byron Area Historic Museum]\n\n{{Kent County, Michigan}}\n\n{{Coord|42|48|44|N|85|43|22|W|type:city_region:US-MI_source:GNIS|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Kent County, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Grand Rapids metropolitan area]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Census-designated places in Kent County, Michigan]]\n", "name_user": "Notorious4life", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byron_Center,_Michigan"}
